observations.recommendation:
We recommended and Management concurred to:
1. Require the accountant to maintain detailed subsidiary ledgers of all the controlling account appearing in the General ledger;
2. Require the accountant to update the preparation and submission of monthly bank reconciliation statements for all bank accounts as prescribed under COA Circular No. 96-011 and prepare the necessary journal entries to record the reconciling items affecting the accounts, if any;
3. Strictly adhere to the provision of Section 20, Volume I of the NGAS Manual in order to ensure reliability of the balances of Real Property Tax Receivable and Special Education Tax Receivable accounts. Setting up of RPT/SET Receivable should be done based on the Certified List of Taxpayers; and
4. Consider procuring an accounting software that will organize, facilitate fast recording and generation of accounting reports.

We recommended and Management agreed, through the MENRO, to:
1. regularly monitor the usage and availability of personnel protective gears, and if needed, consider purchasing new ones to ensure the safety of each personnel involved in waste management. Additionally, as a control measure, encourage each personnel to wear the necessary protective gears and equipment in line with their duties, and provide appropriate disciplinary actions to those who failed to wear one;
2. evaluate the reliability of the perimeter enclosures and assess whether or not a new and much stable fence should be constructed in order to discourage easy access both by animals and the people in the area;
3. strictly limit the access of any individual in the landfill premises by requiring each visitor to log in their information for monitoring purposes; and
4. consider drafting a policy and/or guideline on the wearing of protective gears and equipment for visitors, wastes pickers/scavengers and personnel whenever they are within the vicinity.

In order to address the observations and increase collections, we recommended that the Municipal Treasurer:
1. Improve revenue forecasting by using the forecasting tools provided by the Bureau of Local Government Finance (BLGF);
2. Institute periodic review and assessment during the year to ascertain whether collection targets are attained. The reasons for the shortfall in collections should be analyzed and alternative actions should be looked into to improve revenue projections;
3. Inspect business establishments within the jurisdiction of the Municipality to ensure effective and efficient collection of business taxes as mandated under [Section 470 (d)(4)] of LGC;
4. Maintain and update the tax information system of the Municipality thru:
• establishing a tax roll for each type of tax and revenue imposed in the Revenue Code;
• conduct of tax census and develop revenue data bank; and
• maintaining a systematic and organized records of payments of all taxpayers.
5. Furnish the Accountant the complete and accurate list of taxpayers with the corresponding amount of taxes due and collectibles for the year as basis to record the correct Real Property Tax (RPT) and Special Education Tax (SET) Receivables in the books;
6. Institute measures and strategies to efficiently collect various revenues provided under the Revenue Code of the Municipality, such as:
• sending of tax/revenue bills to taxpayers;
• thorough monitoring of payment of taxpayers and identification and collection of tax delinquencies; and
• strict implementation of sanctions and penalties on erring taxpayers.

